# SAP SO to NetSuite Converter — Project Overview

## Purpose
Convert SAP Sales Orders into NetSuite "Opening SO" Excel format for Double A (1991) PLC (Domestic, THB).

## Tech Stack
- **Backend**: FastAPI (Python)
- **Frontend**: Single-page HTML with vanilla JS (no framework)
- **Database**: MySQL 8.0 (`sap_so_to_netsuite`)
- **Libraries**: pandas, openpyxl, sqlalchemy, pymysql, rapidfuzz
- **Deployment**: Docker + docker-compose (behind Nginx reverse proxy)

## Project Structure
```
web/
├── app.py                    # FastAPI entry point + API routes
├── services/
│   ├── db.py                 # DB connection (reads from .env)
│   ├── import_master.py      # Import 6 master data types from Excel to MySQL
│   └── generate_excel.py     # Core logic: SAP report → NetSuite Opening SO Excel
├── templates/
│   └── index.html            # Single-page frontend
├── temp/                     # Uploaded/generated temp files (auto-cleanup 1hr)
├── .env                      # Environment config (DB_HOST, DB_USER, etc.)
├── Dockerfile
└── docker-compose.yml
```

## Workflow
1. User uploads `.xlsx` file containing SAP report + master data sheets
2. (Optional) User imports master data into MySQL via dropdown selection
3. User clicks "Generate" → backend reads SAP report, looks up master data from MySQL, produces styled Excel output

## API Endpoints
- `POST /api/upload` — Upload Excel, returns `file_id`
- `POST /api/import-master` — Import selected master data type
- `POST /api/generate` — Generate Opening SO Excel, returns `output_id`
- `GET /api/download/{output_id}` — Download generated file
